data.Name: Zip Killer Tool
data.des: ZipKiller is a tool written in Python 3 that uses the built-in zipfile module to perform dictionary and brute-force attacks on .zip archives. It is designed to be fast, efficient, and beginner-friendly for learning purposes. The tool supports saving and loading password lists from a configuration file (zip.conf), allowing users to manage their wordlists and reuse them easily during password cracking
